======================
* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adjoint_representation

L'action par conjugaison donne un morphisme G->Aut(G)
On a Phi_g(h)=g h g^-1

Ad_g est la diff√©rentielle de Phi_g, on a donc un morphisme G->Aut(GG).
La diff√©rentielle de Ad donne un morphisme
ad: GG -> Der(GG)
(o√π une d√©rivation satisfait D([a,b])=[a,D(b)]+[D(a),b])
On a ad_x(y)=[x,y]

Ex: If G is a matrix Lie group (i.e. a closed subgroup of GL(n,C)), then its Lie algebra is an algebra of n√ón matrices with the commutator for a Lie bracket (i.e. a subalgebra of \mathfrak{gl}_n(\mathbf C)). In this case, the adjoint map is given by Ad_g(x) = gxg^‚àí1.

Autour de Lie Kolchin
